            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "A bit more investigation with a cut down version.\n\npxd file\n\n```\ncdef class NameAssignment:\n    pass\n\ncdef class ControlBlock:\n    cdef public dict[object, NameAssignment] gen\n```\n\npy file:\n\n```\n# cython: auto_pickle = False\n\nclass NameAssignment:\n    pass\n\nclass ControlBlock:\n    def mark_argument(self, entry, argument):\n        self.gen[entry] = argument\n```\n\nThe line that's going wrong is `self.gen[entry] = argument`.  If you delete the `Temps left over at end` exception then it doesn't generate the `PyDict_SetItem` code.\n\n`PrintTree` gives\n\n```\n            - stats[0]: SingleAssignmentNode(pos=(simple_flow_control.py:8:26))\n              - lhs: PyTypeTestNode(type=<PyExtensionType NameAssignment>)\n                - arg: IndexNode(type=<(&PyDict_Type)>)\n                  - base: NoneCheckNode(type=<(&PyDict_Type)>)\n                    - arg: AttributeNode(type=<(&PyDict_Type)>, attribute=\"gen\")\n                      - obj: NameNode(type=<PyExtensionType ControlBlock>, name=\"self\")\n                  - index: NameNode(type=<PyObjectType>, name=\"entry\")\n              - rhs: PyTypeTestNode(type=<PyExtensionType NameAssignment>)\n                - arg: CoerceToTempNode(type=<PyObjectType>)\n                  - arg: NameNode(type=<PyObjectType>, name=\"argument\")\n```\n\nI think the issue is that it's putting a `PyTypeTestNode` on the left-hand side of the assignment as well as the right.",
